File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function AntiDifference F_k k,  Next: Variable ev_point,  Up: zeilberger

 -- Function: AntiDifference (F_K, K)
     Returns the hypergeometric anti-difference of F_k, if it exists.

     Otherwise ‘AntiDifference’ returns ‘no_hyp_antidifference’.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Variable ev_point,  Next: Function Gosper F_k k,  Prev: Function AntiDifference F_k k,  Up: zeilberger

 -- Variable: ev_point
     Default value: ‘big_primes[10]’

     ‘ev_point’ is the value at which the variable _n_ is evaluated when
     executing the modular test in ‘parGosper’.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function Gosper F_k k,  Next: Variable Gosper_in_Zeilberger,  Prev: Variable ev_point,  Up: zeilberger

 -- Function: Gosper (F_K, K)
     Returns the rational certificate R(k) for F_k, that is, a rational
     function such that F_k = R\left(k+1\right) \, F_{k+1} -
     R\left(k\right) \, F_k, if it exists.  Otherwise, ‘Gosper’ returns
     ‘no_hyp_sol’.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Variable Gosper_in_Zeilberger,  Next: Function GosperSum F_k k a b,  Prev: Function Gosper F_k k,  Up: zeilberger

 -- Variable: Gosper_in_Zeilberger
     Default value: ‘true’

     When ‘Gosper_in_Zeilberger’ is ‘true’, the ‘Zeilberger’ function
     calls ‘Gosper’ before calling ‘parGosper’.  Otherwise, ‘Zeilberger’
     goes immediately to ‘parGosper’.


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function GosperSum F_k k a b,  Next: Variable linear_solver,  Prev: Variable Gosper_in_Zeilberger,  Up: zeilberger

 -- Function: GosperSum (F_K, K, A, B)
     Returns the summation of F_k from k = a to k = b if F_k has a
     hypergeometric anti-difference.  Otherwise, ‘GosperSum’ returns
     ‘nongosper_summable’.

     Examples:

     (%i1) load ("zeilberger")$
     
     (%i2) GosperSum ((-1)^k*k / (4*k^2 - 1), k, 1, n);
                                n + 1      3
                           (- 1)      (n + -)
                                           2    1
     (%o2)               - ------------------ - -
                                       2        4
                           2 (4 (n + 1)  - 1)
     
     
     (%i3) GosperSum (1 / (4*k^2 - 1), k, 1, n);
                                     3
                               - n - -
                                     2       1
     (%o3)                  -------------- + -
                                     2       2
                            4 (n + 1)  - 1
     
     
     (%i4) GosperSum (x^k, k, 1, n);
                               n + 1
                              x          x
     (%o4)                    ------ - -----
                              x - 1    x - 1
     
     
     (%i5) GosperSum ((-1)^k*a! / (k!*(a - k)!), k, 1, n);
                          n + 1
                     (- 1)      a! (n + 1)         a!
     (%o5)       - ------------------------- - ----------
                   a (- n + a - 1)! (n + 1)!   (a - 1)! a
     
     
     (%i6) GosperSum (k*k!, k, 1, n);
     (%o6)                     (n + 1)! - 1
     
     
     (%i7) GosperSum ((k + 1)*k! / (k + 1)!, k, 1, n);
                       (n + 1) (n + 2) (n + 1)!
     (%o7)             ------------------------ - 1
                               (n + 2)!
     
     
     (%i8) GosperSum (1 / ((a - k)!*k!), k, 1, n);
     (%o8)                  NON_GOSPER_SUMMABLE

